SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 78
BY SENATOR JENKINS
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences upon the passing of Kirby
Shawn Dawsonl, Assistant Chief City Marshal.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the
3 passing of Assistant Chief City Marshall, Kirby Shawn Dawson.
4 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow and deep respect that the Louisiana Senate
5 honors the life and legacy of Assistant Chief City Marshal, Kirby Shawn Dawson of Caddo
6 Parish, a devoted public servant whose life was marked by integrity, compassion, and an
7 unwavering commitment to his community; and
8 WHEREAS, Kirby Shawn Dawson was born on May 28, 1971, to Otis and Sara
9 Dawson, and as a lifelong resident of Caddo Parish, he carried a deep love for his
10 community and a calling to serve others throughout his life; and
11 WHEREAS, he was a devoted husband to his wife, Tasha Dawson, sharing over 28
12 years of love and partnership, and a proud and loving father to Chris, Loghan, and Shawn,
13 with his family serving as the foundation and greatest joy of his life; and
14 WHEREAS, a graduate of Huntington High School, Class of 1989, he continued his
15 education at Southern University and later earned a bachelor's degree in Criminal Justice
16 from Wiley College, preparing for a life of service and leadership; and
17 WHEREAS, Assistant Chief Dawson began his law enforcement career with the
18 Caddo Parish Sheriff's Office in 2002, later joining the Shreveport City Marshal's Office in
