1 2005, where he faithfully served for nearly two decades in various roles, including Court
2 Deputy, Outside Deputy, Court Supervisor, and ultimately Assistant Chief Deputy Marshal,
3 a position he earned through dedication, professionalism, and leadership; and
4 WHEREAS, throughout his distinguished career, he was known not only for his
5 leadership, but for his genuine care for people, earning the respect of colleagues and the trust
6 of the community he served; and
7 WHEREAS, he was widely known as a man who earned respect both in and out of
8 uniform, carrying himself with a quiet strength, authenticity, and consistency that made him
9 approachable, relatable, and deeply respected by all who encountered him; and
10 WHEREAS, Assistant Chief Dawson possessed a rare ability to balance discipline
11 with compassion, authority with humility, and leadership with approachability, making him
12 not only a respected officer, but a trusted mentor, role model, and friend to many; and
13 WHEREAS, one of his greatest passions was his work with the D.A.R.E. program,
14 where he held a leadership role across the state of Louisiana, dedicating himself to
15 mentoring and uplifting young people, and leaving a lasting impact through encouragement,
16 guidance, and service; and
17 WHEREAS, those who knew him best remember not just the badge he wore, but the
18 man behind it; steady, genuine, and always willing to listen, encourage, and stand in the gap
19 for others; and
20 WHEREAS, his presence brought a sense of calm, confidence, and reassurance, and
21 his ability to make others feel seen, heard, and valued is a legacy that will endure far beyond
22 his years of service; and
23 WHEREAS, his impact is perhaps best reflected in the words shared by City Marshal
24 Jefferson, who stated, "Thank you for being my friend. For listening, for encouragement, for
25 guidance, and for inspiration. You make everything better just by being in my life", a
26 testament to the character, friendship, and lasting influence of Assistant Chief Dawson; and
27 WHEREAS, beyond his service in law enforcement, he was a man of strong faith and
28 character, whose kindness, steady presence, and servant leadership touched countless lives;
29 and
30 WHEREAS, his passing on April 6, 2026, following a sudden medical emergency,
